            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
                <p>[- -]ΝΕ[- -] The text is partially preserved: the sherd breaks off on either side of nu and epsilon. Inscribed on the 
                of an askos it is not likely to be a commerial inscription. The text could have been part of a personal name (ownership graffito),
               or dedication.
               
               One cannot be sure with such a small fragment, but it is likely that the text was inscribed on a 
                complete pot rather than on a sherd.
                
                (Inv card) Krasotkina, Bilimovich under the supervision of I.I. Tolstoy, February 1948: [μέ]νε - "Remain!".
                This reading suggests a sympotic context, but there is no reason to prefer it to other possibilities (ownership inscription, dedication).
                </p>
            </div>
